reviewText: Cesar is good as always.
Great episode!!

He's done it again! Inspired me to keep calm , assertive and follow through. Watching his show is always such a confidence booster, and a reminder that I owe to me pets and family consistency and good communication.
Cesar at his best.  The format was a little different than last year's 911 and I liked it!  This was a really touching success story for the family as well!

Ceazar really knows what he is doing. He is amazing and the  lady on video , she was right having a dog is not disposable, like many people think it is , by turning  a dog to the shelter for not behaving well, or whatever.

Great episode.
My family and I always love watching this show. Informative, entertaining, just awesome. Can't wait for season three!
I love Cesar!!!
Always good info - love Cesar!!

Cesar is still the best trainer I have ever found to model after. He continues to grow and has a even softer gentle nature with the dogs. I am always amazed how dogs respond to him and others who use his techniques. My dogs behave better just watching the show with me LOL.

it doesn't get better than learning from Cesar Millan.  He has taught me so much through his dog whisperer and cesar 911 series.  anyone who wants to be a leader to their dogs and in their lives in general with people as well, then learn from Cesar.  His shows are like school to me.  Kathy, Canine Behaviorist

always love Cesar! Kinda miss the Dog Whisperer format... because neighbors and friends are tattling on "bad dogs" there seems to be a disproportionate amount of aggressive cases. I miss the parade of eccentric dogs and their neurotic owners a little bit.

Thank you, Cesar! I am a mom of a 1.5 year old and 4 rescues. Our morning walks are always fun now. People can't hardly believe I can walk so calmly with 2 pitbulls, a husky, and a schnoodle, all while pushing the stroller. They call me the dog mom. Thanks for giving me the tools to be a calm and assertive pack leader (and parent).
Love Cedars shows. I've been a fan for many years. Important information for all dog owners. I'm always surprised by how many "smart people" think dogs will raise themselves.
I really enjoy the show. It's entertaining.
Great show
Love Cesar
Cesar is always good
True  way to handle dogs
I love it

This last episode was a little upsetting to see the black German Shepherd Tasi's unbalanced behavior due to an unbalanced handler.  Near the end, Tasi's handler said she saw potential in her dog, not realizing the focus on "potential" should be on herself.  She also commented that horses are "dumb, stupid animals."  I can not believe the show aired that comment, considering it highlighted an extra ugly side of the female handler.  Poor Tasi.  I am sorry for all dogs who, through no fault of their own, end up with such oppressive, negative environments.
great show, I'm always learning
I love cesar millan. His techniques do work and is not abusing the pet. :)
Love Cesar and his way of training people and dogs.
A little formulaic for binge watching but boy those dogs are cute and cool!
Just can't watch enough of Cesar - over and over - never get tired of his episodes!!
As good as it gets!!!
Cesar Millan is a master dog trainer. I enjoy watching the way he handles every situation with confidence and ease.
What's not to love.  It's Cesar.  My hero!
Very interesting and fun to watch.
I love Cesar 911. It's a lot better than his other show Dog Whisper.
Good information

I always learn something from each Cesar episode I watch. Cesar has sensible solutions that anyone can follow, providing that you put in the time. Loved it!
